<paragraph blockId="26.[189,310,611,637]" box="[189,310,611,637]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,611,637]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,611,637]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,657,860]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Frons and vertex shiny (
<figureCitation box="[499,596,657,684]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 2K</figureCitation>
), almost without microtrichia (like in 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[1085,1281,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1085,1281,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. immaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1294,1394,658,684]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[189,378,693,718]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnicornis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,378,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. magnicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[387,480,693,719]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[541,712,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabanoides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[541,712,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. tabanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[722,818,693,719]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); tergites 2–4 with pairs of white microtrichiose fasciae, covered by yellow setae (
<figureCitation box="[591,678,728,754]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 7J</figureCitation>
): tergite 2 with two small spots at posterolateral corners and indistinct microtrichia anteromedially, tergite 3 with two short, widely separated, postero-lateral stripes reaching lateral margins and tergite 4 with two large stripes tapering and almost connected in the middle, but not reaching lateral margins.
</paragraph>
