</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,644,1228,1255]" box="[189,644,1228,1255]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
LENGTH. Body 10.0 mm, wing 
<quantity box="[547,640,1228,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1294,1531]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
HEAD (
<figureCitation box="[271,369,1294,1320]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 2K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[383,412,1294,1320]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">3J</figureCitation>
). Face largely microtrichiose: microtrichiose stripes along eye margins long, wide, especially at the level below antennae where joined median facial stripe and narrow oblique stripe; face and gena wider than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[474,630,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[474,630,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[639,773,1364,1391]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, gena 1.5 × as wide as postpedicel (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1243,1399,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1243,1399,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,321,1399,1426]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
gena and postpedicel of equal width); distance between eyes larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1242,1399,1400,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1242,1399,1400,1425]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,321,1434,1461]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 0.19 × width of head; postocular orbit wider than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[950,1104,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[950,1104,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1112,1244,1434,1461]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the width of postocular orbit dorsally 0.13 × width of head; postpedicel longer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1039,1192,1471,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1039,1192,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1198,1329,1470,1496]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 1.7 × as long as deep; 1.7 × as long as pedicel; ocellar triangle equilateral without median longitudinal groove.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1398,1570,1632]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">THORAX. Mesoscutum with lateral microtrichiose stripes and traces of prescutellar microtrichia; supraalar setae yellow; mediotergite mostly covered with microtrichia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1671,1768]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">WING. Membrane irregulary yellow-brown infuscated, densely covered with microtrichia that is mainly yellow-brown, except white microtrichia along the posterior edge and wing base; costagium with yellow setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1398,1807,1869]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">LEGS. Setae yellow; all tarsi yellow, metatibia almost entirely dark, with white microtrichia in proximal half dorsally that reach the scar.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1907,2004]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[317,403,1907,1934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 1J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[418,447,1908,1934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">7J</figureCitation>
). Narrower than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[681,836,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[681,836,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[844,975,1907,1934]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(tergite 3 is 1.8 × as wide as long); tergites yellow setose, except black short hairs in posterior part of tergite 2, anterior and posterior 0.33 of tergite 3, and anteriorly of tergite 4. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[852,953,1978,2004]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 10J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[965,1007,1978,2004]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">11J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1019,1059,1978,2004]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">12I</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
